Shadow: 35 <br />
<br />
Ulaire Attea x2 <br />
Ulaire Enquea x2 <br />
Ulaire Lemenya <br />
Ulaire Nelya x3 <br />
Ulaire Nertea <br />
Ulaire Ostea x3 <br />
Ulaire Toldea x2 <br />
The Witch-King, Lord of Angmar x2 <br />
Morgul Skulker x3 <br />
Black Breath x4 <br />
Morgul Gates x4 <br />
Dark Whispers x4 <br />
Nazgul Sword x4  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The fellowship uses mostly Aragorn and Boromir to fight with the 2 Last Alliances and their swords, with the occassional help from Arwen. This way, both Aragorn and Boromir usually have a strength of 10 or 11 even without the use of the Swordsman of the Northern Kingdom.<br />
<br />
Archery can be at 3 for most of the game, with 2 able to be directed, using Legolas and Aragorn&#39;s Bow. Move slowly, stop at the sanctuaries as there are only the 2 athelas to heal with. <br />
<br />
The shadow uses Dark Whispers and the Nazgul Swords to make the nazgul damage +1 or +2 rather than to make them stronger (although every little bit helps!). The Black Breaths stop those pesky healing decks of the Hobbits and the Elves.<br />
<br />
I can usually get 2 Nazgul, or 1 and a Skulker down each turn, which is usually enough to do the job pretty well. There are 11 fierce minions in the deck (14 including the 3 Osteas). Just overwhelm or beat the companions up a little each turn.<br />
